The numbers are placed on a hexagonal spiral.  
For a cell with cube‑coordinates \((x,y,z)\) (with \(x+y+z=0\))

* its ring is \(k=\max(|x|,|y|,|z|)\);
* the first number on ring \(k\;(k>0)\) is  

\[
N_{\text{start}}(k)=3k(k-1)+2 .
\]

The numbers on a ring are visited starting from the eastmost cell
\((k,-k,0)\) and moving through the six side‑vectors  

\[
\begin{aligned}
d_0&=(0,1,-1),\;
d_1=(-1,1,0),\;
d_2=(-1,0,1),\\
d_3&=(0,-1,1),\;
d_4=(1,-1,0),\;
d_5=(1,0,-1).
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 1.  Locate 2026

The ring containing 2026 satisfies  

\[
N_{\max}(k)=1+3k(k+1)\ge 2026,
\]
which gives \(k=26\).  
Its first number is \(N_{\text{start}}(26)=1952\).  
The offset of 2026 in this ring is  

\[
\text{off}=2026-1952=74 .
\]

\(74 = 2\cdot 26 + 22\); therefore 2026 lies on side 2 (the side with
direction \((-1,0,1)\)) 22 steps from the beginning of that side.
Its cube‑coordinates are  

\[
(-22,\,26,\,-4).
\]

---

### 2.  The six neighbours

Adding the six neighbour direction vectors gives the coordinates of the
neighbours:

| direction | cube coordinates | ring \(k\) | offset in ring | number |
|-----------|------------------|------------|----------------|--------|
| \( (1,-1,0)\)   | \((-21,25,-4)\) | 25 | \(2\cdot25+21=71\) | \(1802+71 = 1873\) |
| \( (1,0,-1)\)   | \((-21,26,-5)\) | 26 | \(2\cdot26+21=73\) | \(1952+73 = 2025\) |
| \( (0,1,-1)\)   | \((-22,27,-5)\) | 27 | \(2\cdot27+22=76\) | \(2108+76 = 2184\) |
| \( (-1,1,0)\)   | \((-23,27,-4)\) | 27 | \(2\cdot27+23=77\) | \(2108+77 = 2185\) |
| \( (-1,0,1)\)   | \((-23,26,-3)\) | 26 | \(2\cdot26+23=75\) | \(1952+75 = 2027\) |
| \( (0,-1,1)\)   | \((-22,25,-3)\) | 25 | \(2\cdot25+22=72\) | \(1802+72 = 1874\) |

---

### 3.  Sum of the neighbours

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Sum} &= 1873 + 2025 + 2184 + 2185 + 2027 + 1874 \\
           &= 12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
